<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,608,1067]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,896,922]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Remark</emphasis>
. The externally rather characterless 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[724,900,896,922]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrrhosoma">
<emphasis box="[724,900,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">M. pyrrhosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1148,1221,896,922]" name="Ghana" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Ghana</collectingCountry>
based on a single female specimen. As only additional female specimens are present in the ANHRT collection, the male remains unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,608,1067]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1004,1030]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Distribution</emphasis>
. The species was known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[798,896,1004,1030]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">holotype</typeStatus>
from Biakpa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1137,1004,1030]" name="Ghana" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Ghana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[1153,1373,1004,1030]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref24228" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hacker 
<emphasis box="[1245,1303,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[336,468,1040,1067]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[522,603,1040,1066]" name="Liberia" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Liberia</collectingCountry>
represent new country records.
</paragraph>
